                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="arrowroot_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a plant whose roots can be cooked and eaten or made into a type of flour, used especially to make sauces thick; the flour itself</span></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" unbox="wordorigin" id="arrowroot_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">late 17th cent.: alteration of Arawak <span class="ei">aru-aru</span> (literally ‘meal of meals’) by association with <span class="eb">arrow</span> and the noun <span class="eb">root</span>, the tubers being used to absorb poison from arrow wounds.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
